dist/
*.tsbuildinfo
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# ClaudeView's own derived index — a pure function of .claudeview/*.jsonl,
# rebuilt in seconds. Never committed: a binary blob would only buy merge conflicts.
.claudeview/cache/

# Playwright screenshots from local verification
.playwright-mcp/

# Session rollups are excluded HERE, and here only, because THIS repo is public.
#
# Do not copy this line into your own projects, and note that ClaudeView never writes a
# .gitignore into one — in a normal project sessions.jsonl is tracked, which is correct and
# deliberate. Session rollups are the PORTABLE RESIDUE of the event stream: raw events are
# derived from transcripts that live in ~/.claude on a single machine, so they stay in
# gitignored cache/, and the rollup is the only thing that carries "who did what, when, and
# which commits were witnessed" to a second machine. Ignore it and a laptop clone learns
# nothing about work done on the desktop. See rollUpSessions in observer/transcripts.ts.
#
# The reason to exclude it from a PUBLIC repo is different and much narrower: a rollup lists
# the files you touched and the hours you touched them. That is personal telemetry, and
# publishing it is a privacy choice, not a design one.
#
# (An earlier version of this comment claimed session rollups were "per-machine history, not
# shared knowledge". That was wrong, and it contradicted the code that produces them.)
.claudeview/sessions.jsonl

# Queued/claimed analysis jobs are local runtime state, not knowledge.
.claudeview/jobs/
